          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><text styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" translate="true">Summary</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">This motion-law is </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Continuity" styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">continuous</link><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> and symmetrical.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">It is near to the traditional </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Law-Modified-Sinusoid" styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Modified Sinusoid Cam-Law</link><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">However, because it has only three harmonics, it is smoother at the higher derivatives.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">The maximum velocity is slightly lower and the nominal acceleration is slightly higher than the Modified-Sinusoid motion law.</text></para>
